<br>
I don't hold to the belief that God forbids us to use birth control.  I know that there are some Christian sects that say that scripture implies that, but I'm just not seeing it.  That being said, I personally don't use any form of birth control.  My reasons are:<br>
<br>
1)  I don't like the idea of putting artificial hormones into my body.  My best friend just got off of Depoprovera (sp?) and she's had nothing but problems with her system adapting without the hormones.<br>
<br>
2)  There is conflicting evidence as to whether or not &quot;the Pill&quot; acts as an abortificient.  Some doctors say that it does, others say that it does not.  If there is the slightest chance that I might harm my baby if I use &quot;the Pill,&quot; then that's a chance I'm not willing to take.<br>
<br>
3)  We tried condoms, but my goodness!  Talk about a mood killer!  Plus, my dh doesn't like the way they feel so it was kind of a distraction.<br>
<br>
4)  We also tried NFP, but found that I'm just not disciplined enough to take my temperature at the same time every morning and all the other stuff that goes along with it.<br>
<br>
So those are my reasons.  But I would never say that we should ban &quot;the Pill&quot; or anything like that.  Like I said, there is conflicting evidence, so I can't say one way or the other about whether it *is* an abortificient or not.  I just prefer not to take that chance, kwim?  But anyways...I have to go finish dinner.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
