 here) I have to have fert meds to get pg in a timely fashion. I do however have PCOS and to stop all those nasty hormonal surges that play with my bod... guess what I need. That's right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The pill. While I was going through fert treatments this time around, I was actually put on the pill becauset hey wanted me to have a normal and predictable start date for CD1. It also gave my ovaries a rest.<br>
<br>
I guess what really bothers me about the pill and religion is the Catholic Church. My best friend is Catholic and she has three kids (all c-sectioned). After the birth of her third, she found out that her uterus is dangerously thin and if she gets pg again within two years of having #3, she has a high likelyhood of rupturing and dying. She called me a few weeks ago and said that she may have messed up her FAM. Her youngest is only 10 months old. I have highly suggested to her to get on the pill and top talk to her priest about it, but I guess she feels very intimidated talking to him and she lives two hours out from the nearest bishop to talk to him about it. <br>
<br>
I guess for me, I do not see a problem with it. All they would put her on is progestin (she is BF #3 right now) and that would just plug up her cervix so sperm can't get through. Her mom does tend to tell her horror stories about the pill as well (They will give you cancer, they abort the baby, you will not ever be able to get pg again... etc). <br>
<br>
*sigh*<br>
