<br>
I particularly hate to hear people say that &quot;pregnancy is an inconvenience.&quot;  Having your body hijacked for 9 months, followed by the trauma of labor and then your enslavement by a tiny tyrant is more than &quot;inconvenient.&quot; Personally I love babies, but that's just my little quirk and not something I'd feel good about foisting on others.<br>
<br>
I have a friend who is a devout Catholic and tries to follow EVERYTHING Rome asks and believes BC is a serious sin. She suffers from bi-polar disorder and has to take very heavy meds. Let last time she was pregnant, she had to be off those meds and got so depressed she was suicidal. As it happened, the pregnancy was a blighted ovum (no baby) and ended at 14 weeks - which probably saved her life. Now she knows she can't risk getting pregnant again, because she would more than likely commit suicide and leave her 2 children motherless. So she practices BC now. The fact that her faith tells her this is a sin and makes her feel guilty about it is just sick, sick, sick.<br>
<br>
Gotta run - My tiny tyrant just woke up.<br>
